  "companies": [],
  "statement": "# Minimum Interval to Include Each Query\n\nFor each query point, return the length of the smallest interval containing it, or `-1`.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Example 1**\n\n```text\nInput: intervals = [[1,4],[2,4],[3,6],[4,4]], queries = [2,3,4,5]\nOutput: [3,3,1,4]\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n\n```text\nInput: intervals = [[2,3],[2,5],[1,8],[20,25]], queries = [2,19,5,22]\nOutput: [2,-1,4,6]\n```\n\n**Example 3**\n\n```text\nInput: intervals = [[5,8]], queries = [4,5,9]\nOutput: [-1,4,-1]\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Inputs are sized for local offline execution.\n- Return the value described by the method signature.",
  "editorial": "Track the local choice that leaves the most room for future choices, or sort intervals so conflicts can be resolved with one pass.",
  "solution_notes": "```python\nimport heapq\n\nclass Solution:\n    def minInterval(self, intervals, queries):\n        intervals.sort()\n        answer = {}\n        heap = []\n        i = 0\n        for q in sorted(queries):\n            while i < len(intervals) and intervals[i][0] <= q:\n                start, end = intervals[i]\n                heapq.heappush(heap, (end - start + 1, end))\n                i += 1\n            while heap and heap[0][1] < q: heapq.heappop(heap)\n            answer[q] = heap[0][0] if heap else -1\n        return [answer[q] for q in queries]\n```",
  "hints": [
    "Sort first when relative order drives the decision.",
    "Keep the smallest state that proves future feasibility."
  ],
  "starter_code": {
    "python": "class Solution:\n    def minInterval(self, intervals, queries):\n        pass\n"
  },
